{{Use Australian English|date=October 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox language |name=Dhalandji |states=[[Australia]] |speakers=6 |date=2005 |ref=aiatsis |familycolor = Australian |fam1 = [[Pama–Nyungan languages|Pama–Nyungan]] |fam2 = [[Kanyara–Mantharta languages|Kanyara–Mantharta]] |fam3 = [[Kanyara languages|Kanyara]] |lc1=dhl |ld1=Dhalandji |lc2=pnv |ld2=Pinigura |aiatsis=W26 |aiatsisname=Thalanyji |aiatsis2=W34 |aiatsisname2=Pinikura |glotto=dhal1245 |glottoname=Dhalandji |glotto2=pini1244 |glottoname2=Pinigura }}
'''Dhalandji''' of '''Thalanyji''' (also spelt Dhalanyji, Thalantji) and '''Binigura''' or '''Pinikura''' (also spelt Pinigura), are two closely related [[languages]] from the [[Pilbara]] region of [[Western Australia]]. They are part of the [[Kanyara languages|Kanyara subgroup]] of the [[Pama–Nyungan languages|Pama–Nyungan language fanily]].
