'''International Francophonie Day''' ({{lang-fr|Journée internationale de la Francophonie}}) is observed within the [[Organisation internationale de la francophonie|International Organization of La Francophonie]]'s 77 member states every [[March 20]] to celebrate the French language and Francophone culture. There are over 369 million French speakers on Earth.

Created in 1988, the date celebrates the signing of the Niamey Convention in [[Niger]] on 20 March 1970. The convention established the ''Agence de Coopération Culturelle et Technique'', the precursor to the International Organization of La Francophonie.

